This paper deals with software effort estimation, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The study involves human participants and their decision-making processes, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the potential psychological explanations for the observed effect, which could relate to programming languages (cs.PL) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study involves analyzing data and making conclusions, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY).
